                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182410280028"></xptr>MR. HAYN. On the 2d of October I sent him to Ransom with a cask of spruce - he rang the bell at four o'clock in the morning, and on Monday I asked him if Ransom had paid him; he said No, and told a long tale about having had his pocket picked.</p>
